First off, my joke was OFF topic, read it again.  It had nothing to do with the topic, nor was it to make light of the topic, it was to give me and possibly another a smile after all this sadness.  You want to spend the rest of your life wallowing in depression because of what happened, go for it!  At least I don't call you &quot;sick fuck&quot; for doing so.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I think the melding of real life and virtual reality is for sick fucks actually Dauragon. It was no joke. A reality check might show you this kind of shit is seriously twisted in most normal people's minds. You freaks can't take a second from playing your elves and halflings to go to the many real and signifcant ceremonies to show respect for the dead.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Who said because someone wanted to join hands with their friends across the world (since some of my friends are in different countries) through the use of a VR world is sick?  Why is it ok to come here and post what you think about it and not go out and write how you feel on a REAL message board.  But of course you have no problem with people posting their feelings of the event on this message board, you don't call them sick, even though this message board is just as Virtual as Norrath.<br>
Maybe you didn't realize that doing an in-game ceremony IS taking away time from PLAYING your character.  As I already stated, some of us HAVE gone to real-life ceremonies, read my posts.  Some wanted to do more.  I understand that you feel that a virtual character in a virtual world should not have anything to do with RL.  But if you realized that most people would only do something like this so they themselves can show respect with those they can't physically be with at this time, therefore simply using the character as a tool and the game as an arena.  Please lets not get into a debate of exactly HOW significant these ceremonies you speak of are and who they are significant to.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I would one hundred times rather be forgotten completely than have some sort of bizaare kiddy parade held for my memory in 'GFAY'.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
