What you call a bizarre kiddy parade to some is just a group of friends using the game as a medium to join together and not let the distance we live in real life be a barrier to us doing something together.  Don't worry, I won't have trouble forgetting you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I'm not questioning the sentiment here, just the delivery. Think this through a bit, and once you get over being angry at me, you might just see I said something.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
