<br>
Don't assume you know how sincere someone is in their gestures.  What makes you think you can just log off EQ and make money?  Not all of us are paid hourly and can earn overtime.  In fact, some of us have donated quite well.  <br>
<br>
How exactly is this &quot;toying&quot; with real-life issues?<br>
<br>
Think about people like this:<br>
<br>
You had given blood<br>
You had donated money<br>
You had visited ceremonies in your area<br>
<br>
Yet you wanted to be part of a ceremony with friends you can not physically be with, and the only avenue you have is EQ.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Yes, Jengo, I wasn't calling you a sick fuck, I was calling Vakra a sick fuck... One, for wanting to stay on his lazy ass and hold a service in a virtual world instead of going out, earning money, and donating... And two, for throwing in a Submina ass joke, onto a thread about remembering those who died last Tuesday... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
